  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Diotimus of Miletus, Epigrammatic poet, undoubtedly the author of a
    delightful love poem from the ‘Garland’ of Philip (Anth. Pal. 5,106)
    however, the author of the ecphrastic poems 9,391 and 16,158 cannot be named with any degree of certainty
    under the simple header of Διοτίμου (‘by Diotmos’), they could also have been written by the Meleagrian poet D."
    Degani, Enzo. (Bologna). "Diotimus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider </mads:note>
